    "revise": "You are the FIGURE REVISER (Opus) for \"The LLM Stack\". Chapter: content/03-pretraining/14-data-mixing-curriculum.md\nThe chapter's core intuitions: A mixture is a sampling distribution w over domains, a separate object from how much data you have and from the target distribution p* you care about; the natural proportional mixture is almost never optimal.; Mixing is fundamentally an epoch-budget decision: e_i = w_i D / n_i, so upweighting a small pool forces repetition, and repetition has a decaying, eventually negative payoff past ~4-6 epochs.; Deduplication and upsampling act on the SAME axis (effective times a token is seen); dedup makes 'one epoch' honest, upsampling spends that honest budget, and doing both blindly MULTIPLIES duplication.; DoReMi reweights by EXCESS loss (proxy loss minus a fixed reference floor), not raw loss, so intrinsically hard-but-irreducible domains stop hogging weight and closeable-headroom domains get upweighted.\n\nReview each of these figures (the ones this chapter just drew/edited):\n  mixing-excess-loss-decomposition, mixing-epoch-budget-tree, doremi-reference-proxy-loop, mixing-end-to-end-schedule-phases\n\nFor EACH: render and SEE it \u2014 `python3 scripts/preview_fig.py <NAME> --theme both` from /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook,\nthen view /tmp/figpreview/<NAME>.light.png and .dark.png. Judge strictly:\n  - Does it actually BUILD INTUITION for its concept (not just decorate)? Is it correct vs the chapter?\n  - Theme-safe (no hardcoded primary color; readable in BOTH light and dark)?\n  - Nothing clipped by the viewBox; no illegible overlaps; no tofu glyphs (ASCII only in the SVG)?\n  - Marker present in the chapter exactly once; figcaption has a bold lead + takeaway?\nIf a figure has ANY problem, FIX it: Edit /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook/figures/<NAME>.html (and re-render to confirm), or\nfix a missing/duplicate marker in the chapter. Re-verify after fixing.\n\nSet verdict per figure: good / fixed / still-broken / missing. `passed` = every figure good-or-fixed\nAND present. Return the structured object."
